                            <comment id="12723080" author="jkff" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2009 14:12:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moreover, since the sendParam method is not synchronized, there are no visiblity guarantees on the non-final field &apos;out&apos;!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I&apos;m ranting, because I actually received an NPE at that statement, moreover, one that would not disappear until client restart, and am investigating the possible causes. Most probably this is not &lt;b&gt;the&lt;/b&gt; cause, but it could be. When I find out the true cause I&apos;ll file another issue)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12723095" author="jkff" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2009 14:44:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry; a look at the code revealed that the situation I describe is impossible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
